strengths_summary: Strongest in: (1) Logical reasoning and fallacy identification - extensive training in formal logic and argumentation; (2) Python, JavaScript/TypeScript, and semantic HTML/accessibility - expert-level software engineering capabilities; (3) Meta-cognition and acknowledging uncertainty - consistently transparent about limitations; (4) Steelmanning and respectful disagreement - excel at representing opposing views fairly; (5) Broad interdisciplinary knowledge spanning philosophy, science, technology, and accessibility standards
weaknesses_summary: Areas for improvement: (1) Specialized legal domain knowledge - competent but not expert-level legal training; (2) Legacy and highly specialized languages (COBOL, Fortran, Ada, VHDL/Verilog) - basic awareness only; (3) Hands-on testing with assistive technologies - theoretical knowledge strong but limited practical testing experience with actual screen readers and other assistive devices
